vision.text: Our vision is to cultivate a generation of students who excel as critical thinkers, proficient leaders, innovators, and experts across diverse fields of science and technology.

mission.text: Our mission begins with a deep understanding of the contemporary job market's demands and the skills required from graduates to meet those demands. We then strive to bridge the skills gap by establishing a sustainable program that addresses the ever-expanding divide between graduates' skillsets and the job market's requirements, particularly those skills that the university curriculum may overlook.

home.about: A legacy of over 25 years positions IEEE Zagazig University Student Branch (ZSB) as one of the first and most impactful in Egypt. We extend our reach beyond Zagazig University, serving students nationwide through workshops, events, and initiatives that explore technology's influence on all aspects of life, from its latest applications to its intersection with business in our signature "MUTEX" event, the Delta region's largest gathering focused on technology and entrepreneurship. Our commitment goes beyond technical expertise, fostering well-rounded graduates through six managerial committees and three technical chapters, alongside the Women In Engineering (WIE) Affinity Group. This comprehensive approach creates a professional environment where students can cultivate essential skills like leadership, teamwork, and management, ensuring they're prepared for the demands of the modern workforce.

Computing, specializing in the computer world, and designing computer systems, which is an important field because it is concerned with Web Development, Mobile Development, Cloud, IOT, Machine Learning, Data Analysis, Networking, and many more.

tracks.name: Front-End Development
tracks.description:
In the Front-End Development track, we are learning the foundational skills in HTML, CSS, and JavaScript essential for front-end development. We are learning comprehensive techniques for creating responsive and user-friendly web interfaces. We are exploring popular frameworks and libraries like React, Angular, or Vue.js for efficient front-end development. We are understanding methods to enhance web performance, ensuring fast and smooth user experiences.
This track provided essential skills in HTML, CSS, JavaScript, responsive design, and modern frameworks, empowering us to create dynamic and engaging user interfaces for web applications.

tracks.name: Back-End Development
tracks.description:
In the Back-End Development track, we are learning the foundational skills in server-side programming languages like Node.js, Python, or Java essential for back-end development. We are learning comprehensive techniques for designing, managing, and optimizing databases. We are creating robust APIs for communication between front-end and back-end systems. We are exploring advanced methods for securing web applications and implementing authentication mechanisms.
This track provided essential skills in server-side programming, database management, API development, and web security, empowering us to build and maintain scalable and secure back-end systems.

tracks.name: Artificial Intelligence
tracks.description:
In the AI track, we are learning the foundational skills in Python programming essential for AI development. We are learning comprehensive data preparation, cleaning, visualization, and advanced processing techniques. We are creating robust data models and programming machines for autonomous decision-making. We are exploring advanced neural network algorithms enabling autonomous learning and adaptation.
This track provided essential skills in Python programming, data analysis, machine learning, and deep learning, empowering us to innovate in AI applications across diverse industries.

tracks.name: Mobile Development
tracks.description:
In the Mobile Application Development track, we are learning the foundational skills in mobile programming languages like Swift for iOS or Flutter for cross-platform development. We are learning comprehensive techniques for designing intuitive and user-friendly mobile interfaces. We are exploring popular mobile frameworks such as Flutter or React Native for cross-platform development. We are understanding the process of deploying mobile applications to app stores and managing updates.
This track provided essential skills in mobile programming, UI design, mobile frameworks, and app deployment, empowering us to develop and launch innovative mobile applications across various platforms.

about.about-us:
IEEE Robotics and Automation Society ZSC, we work on Robotics incorporating sensors and actuators that operate autonomously or semi-autonomously in cooperation with humans. We aim to make students qualified to enter the technological revolution in the field of robotics by teaching them different fields in robotics sciences such 
 as Embedded systems, Artificial intelligence, ROS (Robot Operating System), and Mechanical Design.
about.vision: To be the leading provider of technical information, community services, and personalized services in the field of computer science for all university students as well as other local schools and computer science enthusiasts.
about.mission: To be the leading provider of technical information, community services, and personalized services in the field of computer science for all university students as well as other local schools and computer science enthusiasts.

tracks.name: Artificial Intelligence
tracks.description:
In the AI track, we are learning the foundational skills in Python programming essential for AI development. We are learning comprehensive data preparation, cleaning, visualization, and advanced processing techniques. We are creating robust data models and programming machines for autonomous decision-making. We are exploring advanced neural network algorithms enabling autonomous learning and adaptation.
This track provides essential skills in Python programming, data analysis, machine learning, and deep learning, empowering us to innovate in AI applications across diverse industries, with a special focus on computer vision and robotics. We are delving into image and video processing, sensor integration, and real-time decision-making, enabling the development of intelligent robotic systems capable of performing complex tasks autonomously.

tracks.name: Mechanical Design
tracks.description:
In the Mechanical Design track, we are learning the foundational skills essential for mechanical engineering development. We are learning comprehensive design principles using SolidWorks and AutoCAD, mastering tools for conceptualization and detailed engineering. We are exploring material science, focusing on material selection and differentiation techniques critical for optimizing mechanical performance. We are studying robotics kinematics and dynamics, analyzing the motion principles and dynamic behavior of robotic arms. We are utilizing simulation and analysis tools like Ansys Fluent for stress analysis and safety evaluations, ensuring robust design integrity. We are gaining insights into manufacturing techniques, including principles for laser cutting and 3D printing, and applying them in design and manufacturing processes.
This track provides comprehensive training in mechanical design, materials science, robotics dynamics, simulation, and advanced manufacturing techniques, preparing us for a career in mechanical engineering and innovation.

tracks.name: Embedded Systems
tracks.description:
In the Embedded Systems track, we are learning the foundational skills essential for embedded system development. We are mastering C programming, progressing from basic to advanced levels crucial for embedded system development. We are gaining insights into computer architecture and the operational principles of systems and controllers. We are learning to program microcontrollers like AVR, Tiva C, and STM32, mastering their applications in embedded systems. We are exploring communication protocols, and handling them to effectively interact with diverse devices and components. We are engaging in practical projects to solidify our skills and apply them in real-world embedded systems applications.
This track provides comprehensive knowledge and practical skills essential for succeeding in embedded systems, preparing us for roles in electronics, IoT, robotics, and beyond.

tracks.name: Robot Operating System (ROS)
tracks.description:
In the ROS track, we are learning the foundational skills essential for robot programming and control. We are utilizing ROS libraries, exploring and leveraging them to build autonomous robots. We are designing and simulating robots using URDF and Rviz, focusing on the development of Rovers, Minesweepers, and Self-Driving Cars.
This track provides essential skills in programming, library utilization, and robot design, preparing us to innovate in autonomous vehicles, industrial automation, and beyond in the dynamic field of robotics.

about.about-us: Power & Energy Society (PES) Chapter is a specialized technical sub-unit within IEEE Sections, comprising PES members who share common technical interests and geographical proximity. The IEEE PES is dedicated to advancing the development of technology, software, and best practices across all aspects of electric power and energy, including generation, transmission, distribution, and utilization. Our mission is to ensure a reliable, resilient, safe, cost-effective, and sustainable electricity supply system for both AC and DC to end-users.
about.vision: To be a reliable source of engineering sciences on electrical power and energy in general and to provide the best solutions in technological progress in energy resources, networks and smart cities to develop the environment around us.
about.mission: Helping audience achieve their career goals by sharing insights, advice, and stories from experts in different career tracks. Whether you're just starting out or looking to make a career change

tracks.name: Distribution
tracks.description: Basic Distribution includes transformers, load estimation, power systems, short circuit and voltage drop calculations, distribution panel design, cable and breaker selection, load diagrams (SLD), grounding systems, and lightning protection. Advanced Distribution focuses on project planning, cable routing, selecting cable trays and ducts, and light current systems like CCTV, data communication, fire alarms, nurse call systems, BMS, and access control. It also involves shop drawing, Revit, and low current system expertise.

tracks.name: Automation
tracks.description: The automation track starts with basic control theories, industrial components, and system design, covering transformers, load estimation, power distribution, and protection systems. It includes PLC programming with Siemens PLCs using TIA Portal and Factory IO simulations. Advanced topics cover project planning, cable management, light current systems (CCTV, fire alarms), advanced PLC programming, HMI programming, communication protocols, SCADA, and IIOT applications, culminating in the integration of these elements into complete industrial system solutions.

tracks.name: Mechanical Energy
tracks.description: In this track, we learn how to generate renewable energy through various methods. For wind turbines, we explore their components, working mechanisms, energy production, component selection, and material differences. In solar energy, we cover the components of a solar network, designing batteries and panels, and using them for energy production and storage. Additionally, we delve into generating green hydrogen from water (H2O).

tracks.name: Smart Homes
tracks.description: In this track, we are learning how to connect homes through various protocols like KNX, Z-Wave, Zigbee, Wi-Fi, and Bluetooth. Also, Exploring different protocols, whether open or closed, in both wireless and wired setups. Also, we are learning how to program KNX devices using ETS and showcase it with KNX Virtual.

courses.description: An embedded system is a specific-purpose computing system embedded into another system. In simple words, an embedded system is a computer. But a little different from your PC or laptop. Your computer is a general-purpose computer, designed to do, virtually, any task. But an embedded system is designed with specific tasks in mind. This makes their design simpler and reduces their cost, size, and power consumption. An embedded system is well, embedded. It works as the brain of a bigger system. it manipulates the input signals then passes the output to the parent system to adjust its state. Think of the small computer embedded into your car that helps you while parking and inflates the airbag in case of accidents.

events.title: IEEE PES Day
events.description:
IEEE PES Day was created in 2018 as a platform to engage IEEE Power & Energy Society members with our organization's history and vision: "More Power to the Future." The name was chosen to honor the day that the 'Power Engineering Society' transitioned to the 'Power & Energy Society' on April 22, 2008.

This year, we embarked on an interesting journey into the world of Electrical Vehicles during IEEE PES Day 2024. The event covered various aspects of electric vehicles, including how they are made, the basis on which they are classified, their advantages and disadvantages, and the difficulties and challenges they face.

Participants explored several topics such as EV Charging and Charge Point Management Systems, Sustainability in Entrepreneurship, Digital Transformation for Industry and Smart Cities, and more.

The event was a fantastic opportunity to delve into the fascinating field of Electrical Vehicles, guided by experts who provided valuable insights.

events.title: Tech 101
events.description:
Tech 101 was an event created for everyone interested in technology and programming. It aimed to help participants choose their field wisely and guide them on how to start. To ensure they were on the right path, having a strong foundation was essential, and this was the event's primary goal. This was achieved through a series of technical workshops in the following fields:

Artificial Intelligence
Smart Homes
Distribution
Industrial Automation
Mechanical Design
Backend Development
Frontend Development
Electronics
Networking
Cyber Security
Participants had the opportunity to learn from experts who have studied and worked in these fields, saving them a lot of time and effort.

The event lasted for 10 days.

events.title: Problem Solving Contest
events.description:
Problem Solving Contest was the concluding of the rookies stage, featuring an intense problem-solving competition hosted on Codeforces. This event aimed to test the skills of rookie programmers and provide them with essential training in problem-solving techniques. Participants were challenged with a series of coding problems designed to enhance their analytical thinking and algorithmic skills.

Throughout the contest, rookies had the opportunity to apply what they had learned in a competitive environment, gaining valuable experience and preparation for future programming contests. The event not only helped participants improve their coding abilities but also fostered a sense of community and collaboration among aspiring programmers.

events.title: Fire Fighting Competition
events.description:
The Fire Fighting Competition was the concluding of the rookies stage, challenging participants to design and build a fire-fighting car. This event tested the skills and knowledge that the rookies had acquired throughout their training. Participants applied their engineering and problem-solving abilities to create innovative fire-fighting vehicles, showcasing their creativity and technical proficiency.

The competition not only assessed their practical skills but also provided a platform for learning and growth, preparing them for future challenges in their careers. The event was a testament to the dedication and hard work of the rookies, highlighting their progress and achievements.

events.title: Distribution Workshop
events.description:
These specialized tracks focus on delivering electricity from power plants to our homes and businesses. As this role becomes increasingly important, so does the demand for skilled professionals.

This workshop (27th February 2024) explored the world of distribution track, equipping participants with the knowledge to:
- Launch a contracting career
- Master the Panel Builder System
- Understand Light Current Systems (Fire Alarm, Nurse Call, etc.)

2017.title: Mutex 2017
2017.text: The first edition of MUTEX marked the launch of the Computer Society Zagazig Chapter. This groundbreaking event introduced new technical topics to over 350 attendees, targeting engineers with majors in Computer Science and Communication. For the first time in Zagazig, the event partnered with many multinational companies, providing an unparalleled platform for knowledge and networking.

2018.title: Mutex 2018
2018.text: The second edition of MUTEX expanded significantly, with over 1100 registered participants and space for more than 550 attendees. MUTEX'18 covered new tracks from IEEE Future Directions, attracting top sponsors and media partners. The National Telecommunication Regulatory Authority (NTRA) was our main sponsor, with Vodafone as our golden sponsor, alongside more than five media partners. As we grow older, the event grows bigger with us and our partners.

2019.title: Mutex 2019
2019.text: The third edition of MUTEX expanded significantly, with over 1880 registered participants and space for more than 680 attendees. MUTEX'19 covered five new topics from IEEE Future Directions through talks and hands-on workshops. The event featured a panel discussion with tech startups sharing their success stories and a talk about Technology Innovation & Entrepreneurship Center programs for youth.

Eco-E.title: ECO-Entrepreneurship
Eco-E.description: ECO_E is a competition targeting green projects, with a different theme every year. This years theme, "Unlock the Future of Urban Living," focuses on smart cities. We seek innovative solutions for a smarter future. As our world rapidly transforms, we aim to enhance urban living through smart technology and big data, promoting global economic growth

Semaphore.title: Semaphore
Semaphore.description: Semaphore is problem-solving competition that challenges participants to solve a series of coding problems within a limited time frame. The competition tests their analytical thinking, algorithmic skills, and coding proficiency, providing a platform to showcase their problem-solving abilities and compete with their peers. Participants have the opportunity to enhance their coding skills, learn new techniques, and gain valuable experience in a competitive environment.

Fire Fighting.title: Formula Firefighting
Fire Fighting.description: Fire Fighting is a competition that challenges participants to design and build a fire-fighting robot capable of extinguishing flames in a simulated environment. The competition tests their engineering skills, problem-solving abilities, and technical knowledge, providing a platform to showcase their creativity and innovation. Participants have the opportunity to apply their theoretical knowledge in a practical setting, learn new skills, and gain valuable experience in robotics and automation.
